tion","name":"What affects Port Congestion Tracker costs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Freight costs are affected by origin, destination, cargo size, weight, freight mode, customs requirements, port charges, delivery distance, urgency and documentation accuracy."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Carrgo arrange customs support for Port Congestion Tracker?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Carrgo helps importers prepare for UK customs clearance, documentation checks, duty and VAT considerations, port release coordination and final delivery planning."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens after I request a freight quote?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Carrgo reviews your shipment details, checks route and freight options, considers customs requirements, then provides clear next steps and shipment support."}}]}</script>
