<li>Sea, air, road, rail, container and door-to-door freight options.</li><li>Clear quote handling and monitored shipment handover.</li></ul></article></section><section><h2>Why logistics managers choose Carrgo</h2><p>Carrgo is built for logistics managers, owners, buyers and operations teams who need freight answers before money is committed. We compare route, mode, customs and delivery risks so the quote is commercially useful, not just a number on an email.</p><ul class="ticks"><li>Commercial advice before cargo moves, so costs and responsibilities are clearer.</li><li>Mode comparison across sea, air, road and rail instead of one-size-fits-all quoting.</li><li>Customs preparation built into the shipment plan, not treated as an afterthought.</li><li>Practical updates for teams who need fewer surprises and faster decisions.</li></ul></section><section><h2>Freight option comparison</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Best for</th><th>Commercial note</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sea freight</td><td>Lower-cost container and bulk shipments.</td><td>Best when lead time is flexible and landed cost matters.</td></tr><tr><td>Air freight</td><td>Urgent cargo and time-critical stock.</td><td>Best when delay costs more than freight.</td></tr><tr><td>Road freight</td><td>European pallets, groupage and full loads.</td><td>Useful for supplier-to-warehouse delivery planning.</td></tr><tr><td>Customs support</td><td>Documentation, duty checks and release planning.</td><td>Reduces avoidable border delays.</td></tr></tbody></table></section><section><h2>What happens next?</h2><ol><li>Send Carrgo your shipment details.</li><li>Carrgo reviews route, freight mode and customs requirements.</li><li>You receive clear freight quote guidance and next steps.</li><li>We monitor the shipment and keep you updated throughout.</li></ol><p><strong>Ready to compare options?</strong> <a href="/get-a-quote">Get a freight quote from Carrgo</a>.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><details open><summary>Which UK ports experience the most congestion?</summary><p>Felixstowe, Southampton, London Gateway and Tilbury are the UK's principal container terminals and have all experienced elevated congestion. Historical data shows Felixstowe has had the lowest on-time performance (~25%), while Southampton has been more resilient (~54%). London Gateway has faced crane failures and vessel diversions, with turnaround times extending to 3-4 hours at the quay during peak periods.</p></details><details open><summary>What causes UK port congestion?</summary><p>Key factors include: (1) Cape of Good Hope rerouting causing vessel bunching, (2) crane and equipment failures, (3) labour availability, (4) post-Brexit customs processing under the UK Border Target Operating Model (BTOM), (5) adverse weather, and (6) increased container volumes. When multiple factors coincide, delays compound across the supply chain.</p></details><details open><summary>How can importers reduce delays from port congestion?</summary><p>File customs declarations before vessel arrival, book haulage early, monitor vessel ETAs closely, manage free time allowances in carrier contracts, and consider alternative ports or inland routing. Working with a freight forwarder who monitors port conditions proactively can help avoid demurrage and detention charges.</p></details><details open><summary>What is the difference between demurrage and detention?</summary><p>Demurrage is charged when a container remains in the port terminal beyond the free time period. Detention is charged when a container removed from the port is not returned to the carrier's depot within the agreed timeframe. Both accumulate daily and can become significant costs during congestion periods.</p></details></section><section><h2>Related Carrgo pages</h2><ul class="related"><li><a href="/">UK Freight Forwarder</a></li><li><a href="/get-a-quote">Get a Freight Quote</a></li><li><a href="/services/sea-freight">Sea Freight UK</a></li><li><a href="/services/air-freight">Air Freight UK</a></li><li><a href="/services/customs-clearance">Customs Clearance UK</a></li><li><a href="/routes/china-to-uk">China to UK Freight</a></li><li><a href="/routes/germany-to-uk">Germany to UK Freight</a></li></ul></section></main><footer><p>? Carrgo. UK freight forwarding, customs clearance and import logistics support.</p><a href="/privacy">Privacy</a><a href="/terms">Terms</a></footer></body></html>